can any one give me a recipe for a basic shepards pie with just hamburger veggies mashedpotatoes and cheese cheese isn't really traditional so i don't use it but you could put in whatever kind you want if i did i'd mix it in with the potatoes instead of on top this is a great fast and simple recipe taste the meat mixture before you top it i usually end up putting in extra worcestershire minute shepherd's pie pounds potatoes such as russet peeled and cubed tablespoons sour cream or softened cream cheese large egg yolk cup cream for a lighter version substitute vegetable or chicken broth salt and freshly ground black pepper tablespoon extra virgin olive oil turn of the pan pounds ground beef or ground lamb carrot peeled and chopped onion chopped tablespoons butter tablespoons all purpose flour cup beef stock or broth teaspoons worcestershire eyeball it cup frozen peas a couple of handfuls teaspoon sweet paprika tablespoons chopped fresh parsley leaves boil potatoes in salted water until tender about minutes drain potatoes and pour them into a bowl combine sour cream egg yolk and cream add the cream mixture into potatoes and mash until potatoes are almost smooth while potatoes boil preheat a large skillet over medium high heat add oil to hot pan with beef or lamb season meat with salt and pepper brown and crumble meat for or minutes if you are using lamb and the pan is fatty spoon away some of the drippings add chopped carrot and onion to the meat cook veggies with meat minutes stirring frequently in a second small skillet over medium heat cook butter and flour together minutes whisk in broth and worcestershire sauce thicken gravy minute add gravy to meat and vegetables stir in peas preheat broiler to high fill a small rectangular casserole with meat and vegetable mixture spoon potatoes over meat evenly top potatoes with paprika and broil to inches from the heat until potatoes are evenly browned top casserole dish with chopped parsley and serve Cuisine of Africa Coffee